{
  "local_port": 36016,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I verify my Twitter account?",
  "response": "To verify your Twitter account, you need to apply for verification through the Twitter app. Here are the steps to follow:\n\n1. Open the Twitter app on your mobile device.\n2. Tap on your profile icon in the top left corner to access the menu.\n3. Tap on \"Settings and privacy.\"\n4. Scroll down and tap on \"Account.\"\n5. Tap on \"Request verification.\"\n6. Fill out the application form with the required information, including your name, a good-quality profile photo, and details about why you believe your account meets Twitter's verification criteria.\n7. Submit your application.\n\nTwitter will review your application and let you know if you've been approved for verification. This process can take some time, so be patient.\n\nTo be eligible for verification, your account should meet the following criteria:\n\n- The account must be complete with a profile name, a profile image, and a bio.\n- The account must be active and have been logged into within the last six months.\n- The account must have a record of adhering to the Twitter Rules.\n- The account must represent a person, brand, or organization that is of public interest and verifiable.\n\nKeep in mind that even if you meet these criteria, verification is not guaranteed. Twitter has a limited number of verifications it can perform, and they prioritize accounts that are most in the public interest.",
